lenders.occupational_info:
Global Health Professions Microfinance (GHPM) is a national collegiate organization whose members are dedicated to pursuing careers in the health professions. 

As individuals seeking to make a difference in the health professions, we understand the importance of engaging with the international health community at the grassroots level. We recognize the tremendous impact that micro-financing can have on local communities and businesses, and we strive to support small-scale health workers and entrepreneurs in order to directly improve quality of health resources and services in the developing world.  

GHPM operates at the institutional level; each college or university represents a separate chapter that has its own account and portfolio. If you are interested in starting up a branch at your university, please send an email to jason.young@yale.edu.
